China asks the head of the Russian Federal Customs Service not to resort to “abundant” measures while trying to curb China’s novel coronavirus spreading into the country. This is contained in a letter from the Chinese Embassy in Moscow, obtained by Sputnik. The embassy also urged Russia to assess China’s epidemiological situation objectively, in resorting to the “abundant” measures. Coronavirus: Chinese President makes rare visit to patients,… China virus deaths rise past 800, overtake SARS toll China allocates $10.26 billion to fight coronavirus Coronavirus: Confusion in Chinese media over doctor’s… ALSO READ: Boris Johnson reshuffles UK government following Brexit “I express hope that the Russian side will continue to prioritise the long-term perspective and the general state of the bilateral relations and assess China’s epidemiological situation objectively. “There is no need to resort to abundant measures … We count on the maximum possible support from the Russian side,” the Chinese embassy said in the letter. (Sputnik/NAN) SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.